# Garelier nested .gitignore (v2.5.0) — lives at __garelier/.gitignore
#
# DEC-051: Garelier never edits the project's ROOT .gitignore. These rules live
# inside __garelier/ (the only tree Garelier owns). git honors nested .gitignore
# files, so every pattern below is RELATIVE TO __garelier/ and applies to every
# <pm_id> directory under it. The project root stays pristine and removable —
# delete __garelier/ and this file goes with it. No churn lands on the project's
# own .gitignore as the framework evolves.

# Runtime state directory (transient; never tracked)
# Includes runtime/driver/ for autonomous mode pid files and logs.
*/runtime/

# Worktree containers (managed by `git worktree`, not tracked content)
*/_workers/
*/_scouts/
*/_smiths/
*/_librarians/
*/_observers/
*/_artisan/
*/_guardians/
*/_concierges/

# Dock's working directory (transient state only)
*/_dock/

# PM's role identity file (other <pm_id>/_pm/ files are tracked deliverables)
*/_pm/CLAUDE.md

# DEC-020: worktree roles keep their git worktree in a `checkout/` subdir, so
# coordination files (STATE.md, assignment.md, report.md, …) live in the
# container — already covered by the `*/_workers/` … `*/_artisan/` rules above —
# and never appear inside a worktree.

# Re-include the persistent control documents
!*/control/
!*/control/**

# DEC-077 two-layer knowledge model: knowledge is authority like control/ and is
# TRACKED, never ignored. SHARED layer = __atmos/knowledge/ (general __atmos tier,
# a sibling of the <pm_id>/ dirs); PER-PM layer = <pm_id>/knowledge/. Re-include
# both explicitly so no present-or-future ignore rule can swallow them.
!__atmos/
!__atmos/**
!*/knowledge/
!*/knowledge/**

# Local backups
*.bak
*.bak.*
